<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="192" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/1173: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-09T22:00:00+01:00">December 9, 1930—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 9—6:51 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>60. Commission adjourned this morning [<hi rend="italic">afternoon</hi>].<note n="90" xml:id="d192fn90">The 27th and last
                                meeting was held at 3:30 p.m.</note> Delegation pouch will be
                            forwarded via Paris.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>